    <h2 id="why-no-melatonin">Why More Americans Are Choosing Sleep Gummies Without Melatonin</h2>

    <p>Melatonin dominates the sleep supplement market. It accounts for more than 80% of sleep gummy sales in the United States, and its use has increased by over 500% in the past decade according to data from the National Health and Nutrition Examination Survey. But a growing number of consumers, physicians, and sleep researchers are questioning whether exogenous melatonin is the right solution for most people — and the evidence supporting their concern is substantial.</p>

