        <strong>L-Theanine (amino acid pathway)</strong>
        <p>Promotes alpha brain wave activity associated with the relaxed wakefulness that precedes sleep. Works within 30-40 minutes without causing sedation or next-day grogginess.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="info-card">
        <strong>GABA (neurotransmitter pathway)</strong>
        <p>The brain's primary inhibitory neurotransmitter. Supplemental GABA may quiet overactive neural signaling that keeps the mind racing at bedtime. Effects typically occur within 30-60 minutes.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="info-card">
        <strong>Herbal sedatives (botanical pathway)</strong>
        <p>Passionflower, valerian root, and lemon balm have centuries of traditional use and emerging clinical evidence for mild sedation through GABAergic modulation — without hormonal activity.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

