      <p>A 2021 systematic review in <em>BMC Complementary Medicine and Therapies</em> analyzed <strong>9 randomized controlled trials</strong> and found that magnesium supplementation significantly improved subjective sleep quality in adults with insomnia. The mineral's effect on sleep operates through <strong>GABA receptor modulation and cortisol suppression</strong> — addressing root causes of poor sleep rather than overriding the sleep-wake cycle with hormones.</p>
      <cite>BMC Complementary Medicine and Therapies, 2021 — 9 RCTs, systematic review</cite>
    </div>

